This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with sentiment analysis and natural language processing. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as these fields are closely related to sentiment analysis. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as sentiment analysis is often used in search engines and recommendation systems. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as sentiment analysis has implications for understanding public opinion and social media discourse.
